# Video Search

Search inside videos by content using CLIP — no filenames needed.

## Setup

```
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

First run downloads the CLIP model (~350MB). After that fully offline.

## Usage

1. Open `main.py`
2. Change `FOLDER` to your video folder path
3. Change `MODE` to `"fast"` or `"better"`
4. Run:

```
python main.py
```

Then type any search query:

```
Search: lion
Search: lion drinking water
Search: two animals fighting
```

## File structure

```
video_search/
  main.py           # entry point — run this
  scanner.py        # scans folder for video files
  extractor.py      # extracts frames using scene change detection
  searcher.py       # runs CLIP and finds matches in parallel
  requirements.txt  # dependencies
```

## Modes

| Mode   | Frames | Speed | Accuracy |
|--------|--------|-------|----------|
| fast   | fewer  | quick | good     |
| better | more   | slow  | great    |